threepio.tabler
Class ModelTabler

java.lang.Object
  threepio.tabler.Tabler
      threepio.tabler.ModelTabler

public class ModelTabler
extends Tabler

ModelTabler is a specialized Tabler for converting Threepio Documents to Threepio Tables. It is built around using Threepio for conversio from BBF data models to HTML tables.

Author:
jhoule

parseContainer parses a "container" XML body out of a Doc. into an Xtable.

Parameters:
doc - - the doc
param - - the parameter to identify the container by
paramValue - - the value of the parameter to identify the container by.
majorItemType - - the highest level type. for labeling.
orderedLabels - - the labels to use for rows, in order from most prominent to least.
refTable - - the reference table to use.
includeOuter - - wether to include the container element.
Returns:
a table of the information parsed.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - upon anything that would keep from table being made.

makes a table based on "component" tags, instead of the normal way. this is for documents such as TR-143.

Parameters:
doc - - the document to table.
model - - the name of the model to parse out
majorItemType - - the type that defines a row.
orderedLabels - - the lables to use for row names, in order of priority.
refTable - - the bibliographic information, in a table.
Returns:
a table of the information parsed out.

java.lang.Exception - - upon any error.
